fix: correct business query to use existing columns in subscription page

PROBLEM:
- Query was trying to select 'plan_id' column which doesn't exist in businesses table
- Error: "[Subscription] Error loading business: {}"

SOLUTION:
- Changed query to only select existing columns: id, name, plan_name, created_at
- Changed from .single() to .maybeSingle() for better null handling
- Added detailed error logging to debug issues
- Changed plan matching logic to use plan_name instead of plan_id
- Added fallback to 'Plan Gratuito' if no plan_name exists

ADDED DEBUGGING:
- Logs error details with JSON.stringify
- Logs user.businessId being queried
- Logs businessData when loaded
- Logs currentPlan when set

INSTRUCTIONS:
- Execute supabase-verificar-columnas-businesses.sql to check actual column names
- If you need plan_id column, add it to businesses table first
- For now, uses plan_name for matching which is more reliable
